{"title_page": "Leosville", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Leosville|timestamp=20200411073049|year=2020|month=April|day=11|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Leosville|date=11 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox country\n| demonym                = Leosvallian, Leosvalli\n| sovereignty_type                = [[Independence]]\n| leader_title2                = Prime Minister\n| leader_name2                = Sophie Pate\n| population_census                = 148\n| population_census_year                = 2019\n| currency                = Leosvallian Dollar\n| currency_code                = LEO\n| largest_city                = Kweenzlun City\n| ethnic_groups                = {{unbulleted list   | 72% [[Caucasian|Caucasian(European]]   | 13% [[Caucasian|Caucasian(Non-European]] | &nbsp;15% Other(Mainly Asian and European)}}\n| life_span                = 76\n| religion                = {{unbulleted list   | 92% [[Christianity|Christian]] | 8% Other}}\n| leader_title1                = Queen\n| established_date1                = 05/16/2017\n| population_density_sq_mi                = 29\n| population_density_km2                = 11\n| flag_caption                = \n| time_zone                = [[Central Time Zone]]\n| GDP_PPP_per_capita                = $1,040\n| religion_year                = 2019\n| official_website                = \n| area_sq_mi                = 5.19\n| leader_name1                = Eva Kwelt\n| flag_border                = \n| area_km2                = 13.44\n| image_coat                = Leosville Coat of Arms.jpg\n| area_rank                = 193rd\n| GDP_PPP                = $154,000\n| GDP_PPP_year                = 2019\n| HDI                = \n| HDI_year                = \n| conventional_long_name                = The Kingdom of Leosville\n| common_name                = Leosville\n| image_flag                = The Flag of The Kingdom of Leosville.jpg\n| flag_width                = \n| national_motto                = Protect Our Queen, Kingdom, and People!\n| legislature                = House of Ministers\n| national_anthem                = Oh Leosville!<br />[[File:Official National Anthem of The Kingdom of Leosville.ogg|center]]\n| today                = \n| drives_on                = right\n| border_p1                = [[Hamiltonsland|Hamiltonsland]]\n| name                = \n| official_languages                = [[English language|English]], [[Chinese language|Chinese]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Japanese language|Japanese]], [[French language|French]], [[Russian language|Russian]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]\n| capital                = Lincolnway\n| native_name                = \n| government_type                = [[Monarchy]][[Totalitarian]]\n| population_density_rank                = 180th\n}}\n\nLeosville, officially the Kingdom of Leosville is a [[Landlocked country|landlocked]] [[Totalitarianism|Totalitarian]] [[Monarchy]] located near [[Iowa]], [[United States]] and the (recognized only by Leosville)Communist Republic of Hamiltonsland. Leosville split from the [[United States|U.S.]] in 2017. The country is mainly grassland with small areas of forest.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=Encyclopedia of Micronations|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\n== Etymology ==\nLeosville's name was based of a fictional town the founders had designed.\n\n== History ==\n\n=== Native Americans ===\nLeosville was home to a few [[Native Americans|native american]] tribes near the [[Cedar River (Iowa River tributary)|Cedar River]].\n\n=== Independence ===\nOn June 16th of 2017, Joshua Pate declared independence from The [[United States]].<ref>2019 Cedar Valley History Society.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nLeosville sits in the Cedar River Valley near [[Cedar Rapids, Iowa|Cedar Rapids]], [[Iowa]]. It's landscapes are mainly open [[Plain|plains]] and [[Deciduous|deciduous forest]]. The area has been fairly urbanized, with most of the area being covered with suburban housing.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/view/leosville/home|title=The Government of The Kingdom of Leosville|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n[[File:Map of Leosville.jpg.png|alt=A map of Leosville.|none|thumb|The red tint represents Leosvalli Territory.]]\n\n=== Ecology ===\nLeosville is very biological diverse. Some [[Mammal|mammals]] from the area include [[bobcat]], [[coyote]], [[gray squirrel]], [[opossum]], [[porcupine]], [[muskrat]], [[beaver]], [[brown bat]], [[eastern mole]], [[eastern cottontail]], [[raccoon]], [[red fox]], [[gray fox]], and [[white-tailed deer]]. The [[american robin]] and [[canada goose]] are common [[Bird|birds]]. Common [[Reptile|reptiles]] and [[Amphibian|amphibians]] are [[Common garter snake|common garter snakes]], [[Plains garter snake|plains garter snakes]], [[Western hognose snake|western hognose snakes]], [[Eastern hognose snake|eastern hognose snakes]], [[Bullsnake|bullsnakes]], [[Painted turtle|painted turtles]], [[False map turtle|false map turtles]], [[Sternotherus odoratus|stinkpot turtles]], [[five-lined skink]], [[common toad]], [[american toad]], [[Gray treefrog|grey treefrog]], and the [[tiger salamander]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iowaherps.com/county/linn|title=Linn County/Leosville Reptiles and Amphibians {{!}} Iowa Herps|last=|first=|date=|website=Iowa Herps|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=Wildlife of North America|publisher=|year=1982|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\n== Government ==\nLeosville is the only [[Totalitarianism|totalitarian]] [[monarchy]]. Leosville's Queen has the power to make all decisions. The House of Ministers contains 6 elected officials who vote on national bills. Their are also elected governors of the two districts. All four cities have an elected mayor.\n\n=== Judiciary ===\nLeosville's judiciary system is setup so first, a law or bill must come to the governors who will vote if the act is essential. If the act is deemed essential, it will reach the house of ministers. If three or more ministers vote 'yes' on the act, the Queen may sign it. The act will then go into effect at 2:00 PM the next day.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=The Constitution of The Kingdom of Leosville|publisher=|year=2017|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\n=== Military and Diplomatic Relations ===\nThe country has a small military. The Communist Republic of Hamiltonsland and other micronations recognize Leosville as a sovereign state.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Economy ==\nA majority of Leosville's economy is made of fruit and vegetable sales, as well as software. Their top trade partner is the [[United States]].\n\n== Districts ==\n[[File:District Map of Leosville.png|alt=Districts map|thumb|Yellow: Kweenzlun; Blue: Royalma; Green: Lincolnway;]]\nLeosville is separated into three districts; Kweenzlun, Royalma, and Lincolnway.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Leosville|timestamp=20200411073049|year=2020|month=April|day=11|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Leosville|date=11 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox country\n| demonym                = Leosvallian, Leosvalli\n| sovereignty_type                = [[Independence]]\n| leader_title2                = Prime Minister\n| leader_name2                = Sophie Pate\n| population_census                = 148\n| population_census_year                = 2019\n| currency                = Leosvallian Dollar\n| currency_code                = LEO\n| largest_city                = Kweenzlun City\n| ethnic_groups                = {{unbulleted list   | 72% [[Caucasian|Caucasian(European]]   | 13% [[Caucasian|Caucasian(Non-European]] | &nbsp;15% Other(Mainly Asian and European)}}\n| life_span                = 76\n| religion                = {{unbulleted list   | 92% [[Christianity|Christian]] | 8% Other}}\n| leader_title1                = Queen\n| established_date1                = 05/16/2017\n| population_density_sq_mi                = 29\n| population_density_km2                = 11\n| flag_caption                = \n| time_zone                = [[Central Time Zone]]\n| GDP_PPP_per_capita                = $1,040\n| religion_year                = 2019\n| official_website                = \n| area_sq_mi                = 5.19\n| leader_name1                = Eva Kwelt\n| flag_border                = \n| area_km2                = 13.44\n| image_coat                = Leosville Coat of Arms.jpg\n| area_rank                = 193rd\n| GDP_PPP                = $154,000\n| GDP_PPP_year                = 2019\n| HDI                = \n| HDI_year                = \n| conventional_long_name                = The Kingdom of Leosville\n| common_name                = Leosville\n| image_flag                = The Flag of The Kingdom of Leosville.jpg\n| flag_width                = \n| national_motto                = Protect Our Queen, Kingdom, and People!\n| legislature                = House of Ministers\n| national_anthem                = Oh Leosville!<br />[[File:Official National Anthem of The Kingdom of Leosville.ogg|center]]\n| today                = \n| drives_on                = right\n| border_p1                = [[Hamiltonsland|Hamiltonsland]]\n| name                = \n| official_languages                = [[English language|English]], [[Chinese language|Chinese]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Japanese language|Japanese]], [[French language|French]], [[Russian language|Russian]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]\n| capital                = Lincolnway\n| native_name                = \n| government_type                = [[Monarchy]][[Totalitarian]]\n| population_density_rank                = 180th\n}}\n\nLeosville, officially the Kingdom of Leosville is a [[Landlocked country|landlocked]] [[Totalitarianism|Totalitarian]] [[Monarchy]] located near [[Iowa]], [[United States]] and the (recognized only by Leosville)Communist Republic of Hamiltonsland. Leosville split from the [[United States|U.S.]] in 2017. The country is mainly grassland with small areas of forest.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=Encyclopedia of Micronations|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\n== Etymology ==\nLeosville's name was based of a fictional town the founders had designed.\n\n== History ==\n\n=== Native Americans ===\nLeosville was home to a few [[Native Americans|native american]] tribes near the [[Cedar River (Iowa River tributary)|Cedar River]].\n\n=== Independence ===\nOn June 16th of 2017, Joshua Pate declared independence from The [[United States]].<ref>2019 Cedar Valley History Society.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nLeosville sits in the Cedar River Valley near [[Cedar Rapids, Iowa|Cedar Rapids]], [[Iowa]]. It's landscapes are mainly open [[Plain|plains]] and [[Deciduous|deciduous forest]]. The area has been fairly urbanized, with most of the area being covered with suburban housing.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/view/leosville/home|title=The Government of The Kingdom of Leosville|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n[[File:Map of Leosville.jpg.png|alt=A map of Leosville.|none|thumb|The red tint represents Leosvalli Territory.]]\n\n=== Ecology ===\nLeosville is very biological diverse. Some [[Mammal|mammals]] from the area include [[bobcat]], [[coyote]], [[gray squirrel]], [[opossum]], [[porcupine]], [[muskrat]], [[beaver]], [[brown bat]], [[eastern mole]], [[eastern cottontail]], [[raccoon]], [[red fox]], [[gray fox]], and [[white-tailed deer]]. The [[american robin]] and [[canada goose]] are common [[Bird|birds]]. Common [[Reptile|reptiles]] and [[Amphibian|amphibians]] are [[Common garter snake|common garter snakes]], [[Plains garter snake|plains garter snakes]], [[Western hognose snake|western hognose snakes]], [[Eastern hognose snake|eastern hognose snakes]], [[Bullsnake|bullsnakes]], [[Painted turtle|painted turtles]], [[False map turtle|false map turtles]], [[Sternotherus odoratus|stinkpot turtles]], [[five-lined skink]], [[common toad]], [[american toad]], [[Gray treefrog|grey treefrog]], and the [[tiger salamander]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iowaherps.com/county/linn|title=Linn County/Leosville Reptiles and Amphibians {{!}} Iowa Herps|last=|first=|date=|website=Iowa Herps|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=Wildlife of North America|publisher=|year=1982|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\n== Government ==\nLeosville is the only [[Totalitarianism|totalitarian]] [[monarchy]]. Leosville's Queen has the power to make all decisions. The House of Ministers contains 6 elected officials who vote on national bills. Their are also elected governors of the two districts. All four cities have an elected mayor.\n\n=== Judiciary ===\nLeosville's judiciary system is setup so first, a law or bill must come to the governors who will vote if the act is essential. If the act is deemed essential, it will reach the house of ministers. If three or more ministers vote 'yes' on the act, the Queen may sign it. The act will then go into effect at 2:00 PM the next day.<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=The Constitution of The Kingdom of Leosville|publisher=|year=2017|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>\n\n=== Military and Diplomatic Relations ===\nThe country has a small military. The Communist Republic of Hamiltonsland and other micronations recognize Leosville as a sovereign state.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Economy ==\nA majority of Leosville's economy is made of fruit and vegetable sales, as well as software. Their top trade partner is the [[United States]].\n\n== Districts ==\n[[File:District Map of Leosville.png|alt=Districts map|thumb|Yellow: Kweenzlun; Blue: Royalma; Green: Lincolnway;]]\nLeosville is separated into three districts; Kweenzlun, Royalma, and Lincolnway.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "{{Reflist}}", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leosville"}
{"title_page": "Miyazaki (city)", "text_new": "{{Infobox city Japan\n| name=Miyazaki\n| official_name = \n| JapaneseName = \u5bae\u5d0e\u5e02\n| settlement_type = [[Core cities of Japan|Core city]]\n| image_skyline = Route220 TachibanaStreet.jpg\n| image_caption = Tachibana Street in Miyazaki\n| image_flag = Flag of Miyazaki, Miyazaki.svg\n| image_symbol = Emblem of Miyazaki, Miyazaki.svg\n| coordinates = {{coord|31|55|N|131|25|E|region:JP-45|display=it}}\n| region = [[Kyushu]]\n| prefecture = [[Miyazaki Prefecture]]\n| district = \n| mayor = Tadashi Tojiki\n| area_km2 = 643.67\n| population = 398215\n| population_as_of = June 1, 2019\n| density_km2 = auto\n| postal_code = \n| area_code = \n| tree = [[Cinnamomum camphora]]\n| flower = [[Iris ensata]], [[Camellia]]\n| bird = \n| city_hall_address= 1-1-1 Tachibana-d\u014dri Nishi, Miyazaki-shi, Miyazaki-ken\n| city_hall_postal_code = 880-8505\n| website = {{URL|www.city.miyazaki.miyazaki.jpn}}\n| image_map= {{maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=shape|stroke-width=2|stroke-color=#000000|zoom=8}}\n| image_map1=Miyazaki in Miyazaki Prefecture Ja.svg\n}}\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|pic=\n|piccap=\n|picupright=\n|kanji=\u5bae\u5d0e\n|hiragana=\u307f\u3084\u3056\u304d\n|katakana=\u30df\u30e4\u30b6\u30ad\n|romaji=Miyazaki\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Miyazaki'''|\u5bae\u5d0e\u5e02|Miyazaki-shi|extra={{IPA-ja|mija\ua71czaki|lang}}}} is the capital [[Cities of Japan|city]] of [[Miyazaki Prefecture]] on the island of [[Kyushu]] in Japan. Located on the coast and crossed by several rivers, Miyazaki City enjoys scenic views of both ocean and nearby, verdant mountains. A popular resort destination for Japanese tourists, the city offers many attractions, including the [http://seagaia.co.jp/english/conference/ SeaGaia event center] (though the indoor ocean facility is no longer operational), [http://www.miyazaki-city-zoo.jp/univ/en/ the Phoenix Zoo], [http://www.aoshimabeachpark.com/ Aoshima Beach Park], and many large hotels and onsens (public baths). The city is the primary shopping destination for eastern Kyushu residents in smaller towns around the prefecture. The city was founded on April 1, 1924.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.city.miyazaki.miyazaki.jp/gyousei/html/univ/en/index.html |title=Miyazaki City Official Website |access-date=2014-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141015063426/http://www.city.miyazaki.miyazaki.jp/gyousei/html/univ/en/index.html |archive-date=2014-10-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nAs of this merger (but with 2003 population estimates), the city had an estimated population of 365,311 and a population density of 612 persons per km\u00b2. The total area is 643.67&nbsp;km\u00b2. As of 1 June 2019, the current population is 398,215.\n\n[[Miyazaki Airport]] and Miyazaki seaport serve<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.miyazakicarferry.com/11_english/02_route/index.html |title=Miyazaki Car Ferry Routes and Timetables |access-date=2014-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141113054356/http://www.miyazakicarferry.com/11_english/02_route/index.html |archive-date=2014-11-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref>  the city.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Founding Ceremony of the Hakko-Ichiu Monument.JPG|thumb|left|Founding Ceremony of the ''Hakko Ichiu|Hakk\u014d ichiu'' Monument. It had [[Prince Chichibu]]'s calligraphy of ''Hakk\u014d ichiu'', carved on its front side.<ref>David C. Earhart, ''Certain Victory'', 2008, p.63</ref>]]\n\nMiyazaki was the capital of [[Hy\u016bga Province|Hyuga Province]] (corresponding to modern Miyazaki Prefecture) from the 7th century CE. During the 12th century, the decline of the administrative system of appointed provincial governors gave way to warrior bands as the true holders of local authority. The Shimazu clan (who were based in modern [[Kagoshima Prefecture|Kagoshima]] Prefecture) gained control of Hyuga and therefore Miyazaki. [[Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] invaded the Kyushu region in 1587 and subsequently drove the Shimazu back to their base. Miyazaki was reworked into the new political sphere of the [[Tokugawa shogunate|Tokugawa Shogunate]]. During the Tokugawa era, Miyazaki became a castle town, the hub of a feudal domain, and a trade stop within the nationwide commercial network. Miyazaki also became more closely connected to Kyoto during this period.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|title=International Dictionary of Historic Places, Volume 5: Asia and Oceania|last=|first=|publisher=Fitzroy Dearborn Publishers|year=1996|isbn=1-884964-04-4|editor-last=Schellinger|editor-first=Paul|location=Chicago|pages=592-594|editor-last2=Salkin|editor-first2=Robert}}</ref>\n\nIn 1870, Hyuga Province was renamed to Miyazaki Prefecture with Miyazaki being its capital. After the completion of the nationwide railroad system, many new people began to settle in the area.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 1940, the imperialist Sh\u014dwa regime constructed the 37 meter [[Hakk\u014d Ichiu]] pillar upon the legendary site of [[Emperor Jimmu]]'s palace.  Located near Miyazaki, it was originally intended to symbolize the [[Hakko Ichiu|divine right of the Empire of Japan to \"unify the eight corners of the world\"]]. The tower survived the war and is now the center piece of the Heiwadai-koen peace park.<ref>[http://4travel.jp/traveler/godzilla/album/10230307/ Travelogue of Hakko Ichiu] at {{coord|31.9483|131.41457|type:landmark}}</ref>\n\nOn January 1, 2006, the towns of [[Sadowara, Miyazaki|Sadowara]] and [[Tano, Miyazaki|Tano]] (both from [[Miyazaki District, Miyazaki|Miyazaki District]]), and the town of [[Takaoka, Miyazaki|Takaoka]] (from [[Higashimorokata District, Miyazaki|Higashimorokata District]]) were merged into Miyazaki.\n\nOn March 23, 2010, the town of [[Kiyotake, Miyazaki|Kiyotake]] (from [[Miyazaki District, Miyazaki|Miyazaki District]]) was merged into Miyazaki. Miyazaki District was dissolved as a result of this merger.<ref name=\"Plannedmerge\">{{cite web |url=http://www.kokudo.or.jp/new/cities/sub/kyusyu/45.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-09-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070629153802/http://www.kokudo.or.jp/new/cities/sub/kyusyu/45.htm |archivedate=2007-06-29 }}</ref>\n\n==Economy==\n[[Skynet Asia|Skynet Asia Airways]] has its headquarters in Miyazaki.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.skynetasia.co.jp/corporate/guide.html |script-title=ja:\u4f1a\u793e\u6982\u8981\uff0f\u4f1a\u793e\u6848\u5185 |publisher=[[Skynet Asia Airways]] |accessdate=May 20, 2009 |title=Archived copy |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081217233248/http://www.skynetasia.co.jp/corporate/guide.html |archive-date=December 17, 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref> [[Asiana Airlines]] operates a sales office on the sixth floor of the Miyazaki Daiichi Seimei Building in Miyazaki.<ref>\"[https://archive.is/20120530193036/http://us.flyasiana.com/Global/US/en/homepage?cmd=&fid=ABOUT13000&region=JP&city=&searchWrd=%2301#01 Worldwide Offices Japan].\" ''[[Asiana Airlines]]''. Retrieved on January 19, 2009.</ref>\n[[Dell Inc]] has their two call centers in Japan then had opened the one on the 5th floor of Carino Miyazaki Building in Miyazaki.\n\n==Points of interest==\n* Miyazaki Prefectural Office became famous as a tourist spot when [[Hideo Higashikokubaru]], a national celebrity, became the prefectural governor of Miyazaki.\n* [[Miyazaki-jing\u016b]], a shrine in the city's center, is one of Miyazaki's sacred dedications to Japan's first emperor, [[Jinmu]].\n* Heiwadai Tower or \"Peace Tower\" (also known as the [[Hakko ichiu|Hakk\u014d ichiu]] monument), in the expansive Heiwadai park, is a must-see for tourists. Originally the \"Tower of the Emperor,\" symbolizing Japanese imperial expansion, it was renamed for peace after the events of [[World War II]].\n* [[Aoshima, Miyazaki|Aoshima Island]] and shrine boasts some rare rock formations known as the Devil's Washboard among a peaceful beach setting, and it is a popular relaxation and play destination for locals and travelers alike. The [[Aoshima Subtropical Botanical Garden]] is also located nearby and is free to the public, including their greenhouse which features colorful lighting during some summer evenings. [http://www.aoshimabeachpark.com/ Aoshima Beach Park], located seaside with full view of the ocean and Aoshima Island, offers free seating, rental tents, free wifi, and multiple food truck options. Aoshima Beach Park opens seasonally, typically from April to September, and hosts events like fireworks and yoga. \n* The Tom Watson Golf Course was produced by [[Tom Watson (golfer)|Tom Watson]], an American professional golfer.\n* [http://www.miyazaki-city-zoo.jp/univ/en/ Miyazaki-city Phoenix Zoo] is a combination live animal zoo and child-centered amusement park. The zoo offers both single-visit and seasonal passes.\n* The Citizen's Forest is a large park near the Phoenix Zoo. Located on its grounds is the Misogi-ike, Pond of Purification, that is the birthplace of the sun goddess Amaterasu according to legend.\n* The Ikimen Burial Mounds are located in Miyazaki and include the Ikime-no-mori Yukokan, Activity Centre, where visitors learn the history of the burial mounds and learn about ancient activities.\n* Miyazaki City is known for its excellent surfing conditions year-round. Kisakihama Beach, Aoshima Beach, and Shirahama Beach are popular surfing spots all within the city limits.\n* [https://en.japantravel.com/miyazaki/hiking-in-beautiful-kaeda-valley/18242 Kaeda Valley] is a free public park and natural reserve featuring walking paths and hiking trails (various difficulty levels and estimated times to completion). Kaeda is a forested area with a river running through it. There are multiple free parking locations as well as picnic tables and western toilets. \n* The [http://miyazaki-spokyo.jp Kirishima Sports Complex] consists of various athletic facilities, such as running trails, a stadium, tennis courts, an outdoor ropes course, etc. as well as some indoor meeting space. The complex hosts various sports games/matches and events throughout the year, including the popular [https://www.sportsentry.ne.jp/feature/english/event/75060e.html Aoshima Taiheiyo Marathon]. \n* [http://www.miyazaki-city.tourism.or.jp/en/sightseeing/spcat03/spot18.html Florante Miyazaki] is a botanical park that features floral displays and a popular winter lights display. \n* [https://en.aeonmall.global/mall/miyazaki-aeonmall/ Aeon Mall Miyazaki] offers retail stores, restaurants, a grocery store, and a cinema. \n<gallery>\nFile:SeaGaia - Miyazaki Ocean Dome - outside.jpg|Miyazaki Sea Gaia and Ocean Dome\nFile:Aoshima July 2011.jpg|Aoshima and resort area\nFile:Heiwadai tower.jpg| Peace tower with the motto \"[[Hakk\u014d ichiu]]\"\n</gallery>\n\n==Transportation==\nThe [[JR Kyushu]] [[Nichinan Line]] serves the area.\n\nThe Miyakoh Bus Company operates buses through Miyazaki City and surrounding towns. Website is available only in Japanese.<ref>https://www.miyakoh.co.jp/</ref>\n\nThe trains and buses accept payment through any IC card, however, some JR lines, such as the Nichinan Line, only accept cash.\n\nThe city is served by [[Miyazaki Airport]].\n\n==Twin towns \u2013 sister cities==\nMiyazaki has five sister cities:<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.city.miyazaki.miyazaki.jp/gyousei/html/univ/en/content/sister.html |title=Sister cities on Miyazaki City Official Website |access-date=2015-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141105071110/http://www.city.miyazaki.miyazaki.jp/gyousei/html/univ/en/content/sister.html |archive-date=2014-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===National===\n* {{flagicon|Nara Prefecture}} [[Kashihara, Nara]] (since February 11, 1966)\n* {{flagicon|K\u014dchi Prefecture}} [[Tano, K\u014dchi]] (since July 8, 1989)\n* {{flagicon|Akita Prefecture}} [[Daisen, Akita]] (since June 3, 2001)\n\n===International===\n* {{flagdeco|US}} [[Waukegan, Illinois]], United States, since May 3, 1990\n* {{flagdeco|US}} [[Virginia Beach, Virginia]], United States, since May 25, 1992\n* {{flagdeco|ROK}} [[Boeun County]], [[North Chungcheong]], South Korea, since August 6, 1993\n* {{flagdeco|PRC}} [[Huludao]], [[Liaoning]], China, since May 16, 2004\n\n== Notable people ==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=January 2015}}\n* [[Yui Asaka]] (singer and actress)\n* [[Shinzo Koroki]] (soccer player)\n* [[Kosei Inoue]] (judoka)\n* [[Ryunosuke Haga]] (judoka)\n\n==Education==\n*[[University of Miyazaki]]\n*[[Miyazaki Prefectural Nursing University]]\n*[[Miyazaki Municipal University]]\n*[[Miyazaki Sangyo-keiei University]]\n*[[Minami Kyushu University]]\n*[[Miyazaki International College]]\n*[[Minami Kyushu Junior College]]\n\n==Climate==\nMiyazaki has a [[humid subtropical climate]] with hot, humid summers and cool winters. During the summer, the city is particularly prone to typhoons, one of which drenched the city with {{convert|587.2|mm|inch|2}} of rain in one day on 16 October 1939. The wettest month since records began has been September 1886 with {{convert|1259.3|mm|inch|2}} and the driest December 1988, which stands as the only month with no measurable precipitation.\n\n{{Weather box\n|location = Miyazaki, Miyazaki\n|metric first = Y\n|single line = Y\n|rain colour = green\n|Jan record high C = 25.1\n|Feb record high C = 25.4\n|Mar record high C = 28.1\n|Apr record high C = 31.7\n|May record high C = 34.3\n|Jun record high C = 36.2\n|Jul record high C = 37.7\n|Aug record high C = 38.0\n|Sep record high C = 36.9\n|Oct record high C = 32.7\n|Nov record high C = 30.3\n|Dec record high C = 25.0\n|year record high C = 38.0\n|Jan high C = 12.7\n|Feb high C = 13.8\n|Mar high C = 16.7\n|Apr high C = 20.7\n|May high C = 24.1\n|Jun high C = 26.8\n|Jul high C = 31.4\n|Aug high C = 31.0\n|Sep high C = 28.1\n|Oct high C = 24.3\n|Nov high C = 19.5\n|Dec high C = 15.1\n|year high C = \n|Jan mean C = 7.5\n|Feb mean C = 8.6\n|Mar mean C = 11.9\n|Apr mean C = 16.1\n|May mean C = 19.9\n|Jun mean C = 23.1\n|Jul mean C = 27.3\n|Aug mean C = 27.2\n|Sep me